    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>III. OUTPUT DRIVER FOR THE INJECTORS</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The IDM controls when the injector is turned on and how long the injector is turned on by
                closing the circuit to ground by the use of output driver transistors. Each injector has an individual
                output driver in the IDM. The processor in the IDM selects the correct firing sequence, the ECM through
                the FDCS signal controls the timing of when the injection starts and the duration of how long the
                injector is open (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1250603">1.21</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
            <figure id="ef1250603" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="eg1105" filename="../figeg1/EG1105.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 1.21 - Injector Driver Module (Output Driver)</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
